HOUSE BILL 960
C8, K3 6lr3071
By: Delegates Roberts, Acevero, Amprey, Patterson, Phillips, Taylor, Turner,
White Holland, Wilkins, Wims, and Woods
Introduced and read first time: February 6, 2026
Assigned to: Economic Matters and Appropriations
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Economic Development – Federal Employee–to–Entrepreneur Program –
3 Establishment
4 FOR the purpose of establishing the Federal Employee–to–Entrepreneur Program in the
5 Department of Commerce to provide former or transitioning federal employees with
6 certain training, tools, and mentorship for successfully transitioning to
7 entrepreneurship; and generally relating to the Federal Employee–to–Entrepreneur
8 Program.
9 BY adding to
10 Article – Economic Development
11 Section 3–701 and 3–702 to be under the new subtitle “Subtitle 7. Federal
12 Employee–to–Entrepreneur Program”
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2024 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
15 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
16 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
17 Article – Economic Development
18 SUBTITLE 7. FEDERAL EMPLOYEE–TO–ENTREPRENEUR PROGRAM.
19 3–701.
20 IN THIS SUBTITLE, “PROGRAM” MEANS THE FEDERAL
21 EMPLOYEE–TO–ENTREPRENEUR PROGRAM.
22 3–702.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *hb0960*

2 HOUSE BILL 960
1 (A) THERE IS A FEDERAL EMPLOYEE–TO–ENTREPRENEUR PROGRAM IN
2 THE DEPARTMENT.
3 (B) THE PURPOSE OF THE PROGRAM IS TO PROVIDE FORMER OR
4 TRANSITIONING FEDERAL EMPLOYEES WITH TRAINING, TOOLS, AND MENTORSHIP
5 NECESSARY FOR SUCCESSFULLY TRANSITIONING TO ENTREPRENEURSHIP.
6 (C) (1) EACH FISCAL YEAR, THE PROGRAM SHALL SERVE FOUR COHORTS
7 OF 15 INDIVIDUALS.
8 (2) FOR EACH COHORT, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL PROVIDE:
9 (I) SESSIONS ON ENTREPRENEURIAL EXPLORATION AND
10 BUSINESS AND CAPITAL READINESS;
11 (II) ONE–ON–ONE COACHING FOR EACH PARTICIPANT;
12 (III) TRAINING IN BUSINESS PLANNING, COMPLIANCE,
13 MARKETING, BUDGETING, AND PITCH DEVELOPMENT; AND
14 (IV) TOOLS TO CREATE A BUSINESS PLAN AND A CAPITAL
15 READINESS STRATEGY.
16 (D) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL:
17 (1) ESTABLISH APPLICATION PROCEDURES FOR AN INDIVIDUAL TO
18 PARTICIPATE IN THE PROGRAM; AND
19 (2) DEVELOP A CURRICULUM FOR THE PROGRAM.
20 (E) FOR EACH FISCAL YEAR, THE GOVERNOR SHALL INCLUDE IN THE
21 ANNUAL BUDGET BILL AN APPROPRIATION OF $400,000 TO THE DEPARTMENT TO
22 CARRY OUT THE PROGRAM.
23 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
24 October 1, 2026.

